Document: OccluderInstance3D
Path: godot/classes/class_occluderinstance3d.rst
Summary: Defines the base properties and behavior for 3D occluder instances in Godot.

OccluderInstance3D

Inherits: GeometryInstance3D < CullInstance3D < GeometryInstance3D < Node3D < Node

Base class for 3D occluders. Occluders are used to optimize rendering by preventing objects that are hidden behind them from being rendered. This is known as occlusion culling.

OccluderInstance3D is an abstract class and cannot be directly used. You should use one of its derived classes instead:

*   OccluderBox3D
*   OccluderSphere3D
*   OccluderPolygon3D
